1.00	Morphy_number	Morphy number	The Morphy number is a measure of how closely a chess player is connected to Paul Morphy (1837â€“1884) by way of playing chess games. People who played a chess game with Morphy have a Morphy number of 1. Players who did not play Morphy but played someone with a Morphy number of 1 have a Morphy number of 2. People who played someone with a Morphy number of 2 have a Morphy number of 3, et cetera.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2e/PaulmorphyHair.jpg
